{Hearths_with_heat-retainer_hearthstones}

          {hsterm}
           Termite nest hearthstones (holes and channels visible, sandy texture)

          {hscarb}
           Carbonate hearthstones

          {hsclay}
           Baked clay or sandy clay hearthstones

          {hsother}
           Other type of hearthstones (e.g. silcrete nodules)

          {hsindet}
           Hearthstones of indeterminate material

{Hearths_without_hearthstones}

          {emupat}
           Thin, discrete patch of baked sediments with the form of an emu pat (or cow pat), usually associated with charcoal, ash and/or organic remains

          {bakedclay}
           Thin, discrete layer of burnt clay (orange in colour, freshly broken surfaces may be smooth and lustrous) underlain by black stain, may or may not be associated with organic material

          {bakedsed}
           Any other patch of baked sediment, with or without associated charcoal or organic remains

          {ashlens}
           A thin, laterally extensive lens containing ash or disseminated charcoal, with or without associated organic remains

          {ashpatch}
           A reasonably discrete patch containing fragmented or disseminated charcoal and/ or ash, with or without associated organic remains

          {charclens}
           A discrete lens of charcoal fragments (rare)

          {staining}
           Black staining of the sediment that does not correspond to any of the above, no or very little charcoal present, no organic remains, undiffuse boundaries

          {other}
           A cluster of burnt material without clear hearth structure or sediment alteration, e.g. fish hearth, emu eggshell hearth

